Tiles.Name: AdamsCape
Tiles.Description: A carmine tint to the waves. We're approaching Adam's Way, 'where flows the Mountain's blood'.

Tiles.Name: BorealReach
Tiles.Description: Boreal Reach. Is this snow? Touch it, and it puffs to vapour. Your crew huddles close to the warmth of pipe and funnel.

SpawnPoints.Name: BorealBerg
SpawnPoints.Description: Discovered the Lifebergs of the Pale Haunt!

SpawnPoints.Name: BorealBerg
SpawnPoints.Description: Discovered the Lifebergs of the Pale Haunt!

Tiles.Name: CarnelianCoast
Tiles.Description: The Carnelian Coast. Far to the South, the Neath-roof glimmers above the Mountain of Light.

Tiles.Name: Chelonate
Tiles.Description: Another zee-beast corpse afloat. So much carrion. We approach the Chelonate.

Tiles.Name: CorsairsForest
Tiles.Description: Stalagmites loom in the distance like the cranes of Wolfstack Docks, but vaster, vaster. The Corsair's Forest. Our lookouts are watchful.

SpawnPoints.Name: CorsairsFrigate
SpawnPoints.Description: Encountered the pirate fleets of the Corsair's Forest!

Tiles.Name: CryingHeights
Tiles.Description: The Crying Heights, where the Blue Prophets call the names of those about to die.

Tiles.Name: CumaeanCanal
Tiles.Description: Little ships throng the waters here. The crew grow wistful: they swap old stories of sunlit sea. We draw near to the Cumaean Canal, the way to the Surface.

SpawnPoints.Name: CumaeanJillyfleur
SpawnPoints.Description: You have encountered the Jillyfleurs that prey on Cumaean shipping.

SpawnPoints.Name: CanalArchMegalops
SpawnPoints.Description: Discovered the Auroral Megalops of the Cumaean Canal.

Tiles.Name: DawnsEdge
Tiles.Description: Came on deck to find the metal sharp with sparks. Ozonal coronas haunt the ship. This is Dawn's Edge.

SpawnPoints.Name: DawnFrigate
SpawnPoints.Description: You have encountered the  Glorious Frigates.

SpawnPoints.Name: DawnDreadnaught
SpawnPoints.Description: Discovered the Glorious Dreadnoughts.

Tiles.Name: genericSouthOfPillaredSea
Tiles.Description: Fathoms below, miles above.

Tiles.Name: DemauxsGate
Tiles.Description: Here the wilder airs mingle with the airs of the near reaches. Demeaux's Gate, named for a navigator lost above. How did his bones come below?

Tiles.Name: EmpireofHands
Tiles.Description: We approach the Empire of Hands. Let us clasp our souls tight, lest the Pentecost Apes take them from us.

Tiles.Name: genericEastOfStormbones
Tiles.Description: Frostfound, vast and chilly. A fortress sieged by questions, answers, and riddles.

SpawnPoints.Name: FrostfoundBerg
SpawnPoints.Description: Discovered the Lifebergs of Frostfound!

Tiles.Name: GossamerWay
Tiles.Description: A floating strand of web caresses your face. The air hints at spiders.

Tiles.Name: IronRepublic
Tiles.Description: Sizzling vapours rise from the sea. Time slips sideways. A coil of rope has stung a stoker, and his fellows beat it to death. We are under the hand of the Iron Republic.

SpawnPoints.Name: IronRepublicDreadnaught
SpawnPoints.Description: You have encountered the Iron Republic Dreadnaughts.

SpawnPoints.Name: IronRepublicUnfinishedRevolutionaries
SpawnPoints.Description: Discovered the Unfinished Revolutionaries of the Iron Republic.

Tiles.Name: genericEastOfChelonate
Tiles.Description: The water is sluggish with hyphal threads. Violet vegetable bulks break the surface. Myceligaea!

Tiles.Name: PalmerstonsReach
Tiles.Description: Palmerston's Reach. There is brimstone on the wind.

Tiles.Name: PillaredSea
Tiles.Description: Strange puffs of warmth from the air behind the ice. This is the Pillared Sea, where Irem will lie. Lies. Has always lain.

Tiles.Name: PrinciplesofCoral
Tiles.Description: The Principles of Coral. The corpse-rainbow glow from beneath the waves echoes the false-stars above.

SpawnPoints.Name: PrinciplesShark
SpawnPoints.Description: Found the Bound-Sharks of Errant's Gyrus!

TerrainData.Name: Curious humped shapes like conjoined whales lie

Tiles.Name: PromisedSea
Tiles.Description: The Promised Sea. All through this place, the song of the Drownies lies shivering-sweet along the wind.

SpawnPoints.Name: PromisedSeaFluke
SpawnPoints.Description: Discovered the Lorn Flukes of the Promised Sea!

Tiles.Name: Rattsey
Tiles.Description: Scuttering and chittering in the corners of the hold. Humped shapes on the deck rail. Rattsey air emboldens vermin.

Tiles.Name: SaltSteppes
Tiles.Description: The Salt Steppes. This is the domain of the New Khanate, whose ancestors came here long before London fell...

SpawnPoints.Name: SaltSteppesTrimaran
SpawnPoints.Description: Discovered the Trimarans of the Khanate.

SpawnPoints.Name: SaltSteppesTrimaran
SpawnPoints.Description: Discovered the Trimarans of the Khanate.

SpawnPoints.Name: SaltSteppesTrimaran
SpawnPoints.Description: Discovered the Trimarans of the Khanate.

Tiles.Name: SeaofAutumns
Tiles.Description: The mists of the Sea of Autumn get into the eyes, the heart. It is not unusual to find yourself in unsuspected tears.

Tiles.Name: SeaofLilies
Tiles.Description: We watch for fungal-pads in the Sea of Lilies. There is a prison here, guarded by knot-oracles...

Tiles.Name: SeaOfStatues
Tiles.Description: We have entered the Sea of Statues. Giants gape at us. Kingeater's Castle rises ahead, where fools give up their future.

Tiles.Name: SeaofVoices
Tiles.Description: 'We hear those voices that will not be drowned.' This is the Sea of Voices: we are close to Polythreme, where nothing is truly dead.

Tiles.Name: SeaOfWings
Tiles.Description: Milliner-bats perch on the funnel, gaudy with stolen plumage. This must be the Feathered Sea.

Tiles.Name: ShepherdWash
Tiles.Description: Shepherd's Wash, the salty hinterland of London, home to hermits, nuns and shadowy business.

Tiles.Name: SouthernArchipelago
Tiles.Description: Home waters. Zailors dawdle at the rail, watching for the lights of London.

TerrainData.Name: A homely village huddles around a harbour
HuntersKeep
TerrainData.Description: A grand house rises over a humble isle

TerrainData.Name: Low Barnet
TerrainData.Description: A Placeholder city, its towering features squint and fade before you, a wonder of momentary existance.

Tiles.Name: SouthernWall
Tiles.Description: A buttery bloom of light on the southern horizon! You approach Varchas, the Mirrored City.

Tiles.Name: SouthernWallTiling
Tiles.Description: This part of the Unterzee (The Southern Wall) has not yet been created!

Tiles.Name: StamfordsExpanse
Tiles.Description: The false-stars above are feral amber, like tigers' eyes. Stamford's Expanse, named for one who lost his child to cats.

Tiles.Name: StonesoulIsles
Tiles.Description: A baked breeze rises, the improbable scent of stone out of some distant desert. You are close to the Salt Lions.

Tiles.Name: Stormbones
Tiles.Description: We enter Stormbones. St Eligius sends his fire to dance in the air, on deck. Very far away we see the great light of the Ragged Crow.

SpawnPoints.Name: StormbonesMoth
SpawnPoints.Description: Discovered the Tyrant Moths of The Ragged Crow.

Tiles.Name: genericEastOfEmpireofHands
Tiles.Description: And now we enter the Calumnies. There is a wild and glorious scent in the air. A kind of light. Why do zailors fear this place?

Tiles.Name: TheSnares
Tiles.Description: Creeping tendrils of fungus, zee-weed, unnamable flora. We enter the Snares.

Tiles.Name: TombColonies
Tiles.Description: Dust, echoes: even a sepia tint to the air. These are the waters around the Tomb-Colonies.

SpawnPoints.Name: TombPinnace
SpawnPoints.Description: Discovered the flocks of bats outside the Tomb Colonies.

SpawnPoints.Name: TombBats
SpawnPoints.Description: Discovered the flocks of bats outside the Tomb Colonies.

SpawnPoints.Name: TombMegalops
SpawnPoints.Description: Discovered a group of Auroral Megalops outside the Tomb Colonies.

SpawnPoints.Name: TombBats
SpawnPoints.Description: Discovered the flocks of bats outside the Tomb Colonies.

SpawnPoints.Name: TombBats
SpawnPoints.Description: Discovered the flocks of bats outside the Tomb Colonies.

Tiles.Name: VoidsApproach
Tiles.Description: This must be Void's Approach. The air crackles with frosty radiations. To the North, the false-stars fail in the darkness.

SpawnPoints.Name: MtNomad
SpawnPoints.Description: discovered Mt Nomad, the black glass mountain that eats ships.

Tiles.Name: GenericRocks1
Tiles.Description: No landlubber would notice the change. But you feel the air prickle on your skin. Somewhere new.

SpawnPoints.Name: GenericBats
SpawnPoints.Description: Encountered the colony of bats!

Tiles.Name: GenericRocks2
Tiles.Description: Here the slate-black sea is like rippled glass, spiked with light from the roof.

Tiles.Name: GenericRocks3
Tiles.Description: The world is webbed with invisible lines. You've crossed one. Tighten them, and it would split like a fruit.

SpawnPoints.Name: GenericJillyfleur
SpawnPoints.Description: Encountered a group of Jillyfleurs!

SpawnPoints.Name: GenericBats
SpawnPoints.Description: Encountered a group of bats!

Tiles.Name: Generic_Reefs
Tiles.Description: Spined towers rear in the light of the false-stars. Ware reefs.

Tiles.Name: Generic_Ruins
Tiles.Description: The wind carries the echo of distant chants. Long-dead priests still count the hours in this place.

Tiles.Name: Generic_Shroomy1
Tiles.Description: A sudden fog of spores! Zailors sneeze. The sound echoes flatly in the soupy air.

Tiles.Name: GenericEye
Tiles.Description: Something forgotten is here.

Tiles.Name: Generic_Volcanic1
Tiles.Description: The zee here is warm. Bubbles rise and burst with lazy menace. The fire in the earth is restless.
